## 2. User Story Context

Use this section to merge the user story into the functional requirement so the FR explains the feature intent, user value, and scenario context without requiring readers to open the story first.

- **Story statement:** As a `<actor / persona>`, I want `<capability / behavior>`, so that `<business or user outcome>`.
- **Story source:** [US-TBD](../../../04-planning/product-backlog.md#us-tbd), PRD story file, backlog item, stakeholder note, or `Not available - evidence gap recorded`.
- **Feature objective:** Plain-language description of what this feature enables and why it matters.
- **User value / business value:** Operational, compliance, productivity, service, reporting, or customer value expected from this behavior.
- **Primary user scenario:** Narrative of the normal user journey or system scenario this FR supports.
- **Story-derived constraints:** Story notes, assumptions, exclusions, or scope boundaries that shape this FR.
- **Story-derived acceptance focus:** Summarize the story acceptance criteria that this FR must satisfy; keep full testable criteria in Section 4.

## 3. Behavior Detail

- **Actor(s):** Primary actor and any supporting actor/system.
- **Trigger:** Event, user action, schedule, integration message, or business condition that starts the behavior.
- **Preconditions:** Required state, permissions, configuration, data, upstream availability, or operational context.
- **System behavior:** Observable behavior the system shall perform. Avoid database, framework, or UI-layout design unless it is required product behavior.
- **Inputs / data captured:** Data fields, source, required/optional status, format/lookup dependencies, and validation rules.
- **Outputs / state changes:** Link output records, status changes, notifications, reports, exports, events, audit entries, or visible confirmations.
- **Permissions / access rules:** Roles, policies, ownership, segregation, or visibility rules that affect the behavior.
- **Audit / history behavior:** Required when the action changes regulated, operational, financial, security, personal, or otherwise sensitive data; otherwise record `Not applicable` with rationale.
- **Business rules:** [BRULE-001](../../functional-requirements.md#7-business-rules); list each rule that constrains the behavior.
- **Exception paths:** Permission denied, missing/invalid input, duplicate/conflict, partial completion, upstream failure, timeout, offline/fallback, cancel/retry, and unsupported state.

## 4. Acceptance Criteria

Each `Must` FR needs one happy path, one alternate/edge path, and one permission/error path unless explicitly justified. Include expected output, audit/history behavior, and no-change/rollback rule where relevant.
Where a linked user story has acceptance criteria, merge the relevant story criteria into these FR criteria and make them observable, testable, and traceable to the FR ID.

